caption: This is favorite milk tea spot in town. They pearls/bubbles are chewy and delicious. Their Milktea is not that sweet and with no dairy milk which the only milk I can take. The staff always friendly and helpful every time I go in.
Their brown sugar tea is SO good, but I feel like their boba should have more flavor. Their drinks are also beautiful!

The matcha based dessert/drink place has great service and pretty good drinks. I order a matcha mousse jade tea and it was too bitter for me, so the workers offered to add more sugar for me. They made sure that it was sweet enough and that it was good for my liking.

I've trekked many a time to UWS from Brooklyn because Shiny Tea is THE place. When Hanlin, originator of all that is good and boba, opened up a location in my hometown, it brought me back to what boba should be. Good, quality tea, qq bobas.  Shiny Tea is  *authorized* by Hanlin, so their teas and bobas are about the same high quality here. Even the cute panda bobas!  It's definitely worth coming here if you're in the area, and clearly if your not. There was even a state trooper who was clearly a regular who came here so....yea, you need to get your butt here.

This is a very unique boba place. They have the classic flavors along with newer, hip flavors. They are very flexible with orders and there's ways to spin a classic bbt orders. They have crystal boba (unheard of on the east coast; even better than honey/normal boba). Would definitely come back again if I'm in the area!

So lucky to have this Taiwanese boba place in the UWS. I can actually taste the tea in their milk teas and I like their egg pudding. I get $10 off $15 coupons from Grubhub so I buy 3 teas at a time and save them for later. Don't forget to ask for a stamp card!

Love the drinks here!!! The drinks at Shiny Tea is always consistent and great quality. I had the chocolate boba tea and it’s so chocolaty! The place usually gets packed during the weekend afternoons, but they let you pre-order online so you won’t have to wait that long! They are definitely the best boba tea place in NY! Friendly staff too!

Best boba in the UWS; they use quality tea from Taiwan. Tieguanyin milk tea is top notch.  Temporarily closed from September 1, 2019.  Update: they had reopened soon after my previous post, are still running as of September 2020, and still produce great milk tea!
My daughter said it was too sweet.  She said 3 n a half stars lol

This is the time to go to Shiny Tea UWS. ITS QUIET AT 11:30 and only 3 people at pick up window parking on ave 51  St Our first time here today after months of waiting for a quiet time . We ordered 1000 pancake , shrimp wonton ,soup chiayi chicken rice and pickle and dan Dan noodles Wow marvelous Can't wait to return all the talk was true of JOYS EXCELLENCE .

I tried to use the app to order a lunch pick-up but it wasn't cooperating so I just called them, spoke to a person (from a shop across the street), and picked up my delicious lunch 12 minutes later.  It was so easy!
What a cute tea store! The staff here are really great.
Very friendly service. They upgraded our drinks to a larger size, and because they made an error they gave us a free drink. Drink was delicious. Will be coming back again.
Drinks are good but waited forever because there's only one worker and he's kinda slow
My drink tasted great but the wait was pretty long.
ahh i go to shiny tea a lot and i love it so much!! best boba in the uws

This place is great. A huge variety and the staff is super nice. I swear I go here at least twice a week and I've never been disappointed. Edit: I change my mind about not being disappointed. Twice now I waited in line for about 15 minutes and didn't move a single inch. I don't know what's going on. People were leaving the line after 10 minutes or so. Shiny tea has to get itself together before they lose more business.
Great and authentic Taiwanese bubble tea place perfectly works for my craving. Thumb up!
Boba is chewy. Very authentic!! Highly recommend to come and try!
Quality Taiwanese tea makes delicious boba & white pearl drinks! Excellent <3
Best bubble tea shop I have been to in NYC. A million options, highly customizable drinks, and great customer service. Highly recommend the passion fruit tea! Delicious 😊😊😊
Great local little place. Amazing customer service

(Translated by Google) Best bubble tea shop around the area! My favorite place to grab a drink. Very friendly staff and great service.  The best pearl milk tea nearby.  (Original) Best bubble tea shop around the area!  My favorite place to grab a drink. Very friendly staff and great service.  附近最好喝的珍珠奶茶. 大推

I just waited online for 10–15 mins for bubble tea for them to tell me they don’t have any BOOBA LEFT!! I am highly annoyed, I wouldn’t really recommend to the service. I traveled 30 blocks to come here. Really disappointed!!
I love it
They have so many different selections of teas, definitely the best in town!

This is my fav bubble tea spot in the neighborhood! I was disappointed when it closed for few weeks but it's OPEN again! I like the classic bubble tea but I love the TieQuanYin Tea + bubble even more! Also, the price is reasonable unlike all the other bubble tea shops in the city now. Highly recommend this place!
As a frequent bubble tea drinker, this place really exceeded my expectation. They use high quality tea  and their tapioca always taste fresh and with the right chewy texture. Highly recommended!
Best bubble tea I’ve ever had!!!
Delicious and good service here. Reopen this coming Sunday Oct 5.
BEST BOBA PLACE EVER! I rank this #1 out of all the boba places on the uws and trust me i’ve tried A LOT of boba.
cool place
Very good boba place!

Wow. I love this place! There is a very very big variety of things for your drink and what to put inside. I even learned some new stuff lol. So far the best boba place in NYC for me! You get to customize your drink with the amount of sugar, the amount of ice and of course what you want it to be and what to put inside so that the drink is just right for you. In my experience they re-checked my orders and labeled the different drinks so I know which ones which. Definitely a place you should try!
Get the brown sugar milk tea! Best in morning side heights

The best boba place I've found in NYC so far (and I've tried quite a few already). Their fruit teas are made with juice concentrate (not syrup, yay) and their lemon is freshly squeezed for drinks that have lemon. Their menu is quite extensive too, and it has a lot of different kind of teas, including unique milk teas as well as fruit teas. I got their mango green tea without ice and without sugar, and it was quite good. I think their tea could be stronger, but it was quite good as was. Menu prices include tax which is great, and my tea was reasonably priced. Not bad for quality and quantity!
So good!!

This place offers the best bubble tea in all of NYC! Sadly the Flushing location closed down so I have to go here for it now. The credit card minimum is $10. The staff here is really friendly and accommodating. I recommend the bubble tea with panda bubbles, I believe that’s what it’s called.
cancel my order without calling lol，worst
Nice place👌🏼
Best bubble tea in NYC!
The best bubble tea

This is a great place to go after school, they are extremely polite and are always very gracious, even if I or one of my friends is being rude. If you are ever in the area I would highly recommend checking out this hole in the wall (literally) boba shop. My personal favorite is the caramel milk tea with panda boba.

Hole-in-the-wall and easy to miss, but one of the best bubble tea options in the area. I love that they offer sago (mini tapioca) as a topping! My go-to is the Tie Guan Yin Milk Tea (a type of oolong tea).
the best bobble tea I have ever had, great service.

I love this place, not only because it feel like a little secret hole-in-the-wall only I know about, but because it has apple vinegar drinks(!). It sounds weird, but give it a shot - apple vinegar juice + coconut jelly is the way to go. Their brown sugar milk tea is pretty good as well, and they're known for their panda bubbles (mixed large and small tapioca). Card minimum is like $10, so bring cash or a friend or two.
Good bubble tea at a normal price.
After one visit this is the only place I go for bubble tea.
Good tea, fat friendly service.
Favorite boba place near Columbia
Best bubble tea I've had in the city. Really amazing and authentic the staff is always friendly and helpful!
Decent bubble tea but we received condescending and rude service.
Panda milk tea with red bean (30% or no sugar), great!
Great place for bubble tea
Tiny little shop with a line out the door but the tea was good. Personally not a fan of the white pearl but an interesting twist nonetheless
Amazing Loved it!!! Highly recommend!

Tiny little bubble tea place.  So small there can be no more than 4  customers in the "store" at a time.  Oftentimes, you will need to wait outside for your turn to place an order.  This may be an issue when the weather gets colder or hotter when you have to stand in the sun/heat.  I like how they have white and black bubbles too rather than just the typical black bubbles.
Mmmiss my boba tea!!! Matcha au lait! So good!
Good tea!
If your thinking about going just go. You will be satisfied!
(Translated by Google) Taiwanese tea to the place!  (Original) 到地的台湾茶!

Went here for the first time, absolutely LOVED the taro milk tea with boba. It tastes so much better than the majority of other boba tea places out there, not too sweet, and the boba was actually made correctly and not hard in the middle. Very reasonably priced. I’ll definitely be coming back!
Awesome bubble tea! 😊

Always friendly service. Tiny spot so it gets cramped with any line, but they’ve never burnt my tea like other places. Usually get grapefruit juice or one of the plain teas. $10 card minimum, slight hassle but you can purchase a $10 gift card if you don’t have cash and use the leftover later. Student discount with ID.

I go here at least twice a week. I always get the honey black tea either hot or cold with 30% sweetness and less ice and with boba. It’s so good! It doesn’t taste as processed or over sweet as other bubble tea places that I’ve tried. I highly recommend.
According to my Taiwanese friend, the teas from this place are pretty authentic. My favorite one is  the milk tea with panda bubbles. They also accept student id for discount.

Outstanding bubble tea on the Upper West Side. Service is pretty slow, as there are only 2 workers and they handle one order at a time, but the tea is generally worth the wait.  It's the quality of their tea and their boba that makes this place stand out above the rest in this neighborhood.

I have been coming here for few months already . Have to say I am in love with the taste of the bubble tea here. My personal favorite is Mango Green Tea with Boba Bubbles. The green tea has a quality taste to it. I sometimes catch myself buy tea from here 3-4 times out of the week. Would definitely recommend this place to the bobble tea lovers. Place extremely small with no place to sit down and enjoy the tea. But definitely enough space to be in and out and still enjoy the bubble tea. Place looks and feels very clean and staff is super helpful and friendly.

Shiny tea is my favorite bubble tea store, the price is a little higher than other bubble tea stores, but their tea is SOOO good it is worth it! I highly recommended trying it, (my favorite tea is panda milk tea, not made with panda milk, but it is very good if you ever come here give it a try!)

This place has an extensive menu but a tiny, tiny location. I walked right past it the first time. There's barely room for three people to stand inside! The drinks were made quickly and were delicious, though. They only accept credit over ten dollars, so if you're only getting one drink, bring cash.
my favorite boba place in town so far. good menu, super quick service.
Large selection of bubble tea with real brewed teas. Should definitely try with the white bubbles instead of the regular boba.
Very large menu for Boba Tea. Good service and great teas. Very small inside so plan on ordering and taking to go
Some of the best bubble tea on the UWS. Always fast service, too.

Lovely Taiwanese Bubble Tea
Great staff. The bubble tea is delicious.
Pretty much the best milk tea spot in upper west.
Great authentic Taiwanese tea flavors and toppings! Love having this shop around in the neighborhood -- I no longer need to go to Flushing for great bubble tea.
Extensive menu with the best boba in the neighborhood.
Simple place that's easy to miss if you're not looking for it. Good milk tea
Worst ever

This is a new hole-in-the-wall place serving a very large selection of Taiwanese tea (milk tea/boba/bubble tea). It is a very tiny place that is easy to miss. There are no chairs or tables, but a tiny counter where you could rest your tea. Regardless, it's a quick place to grab some good milk tea. We liked the tea.
